args: With Ramona in tow, {player_name} and\nfriends reach a mountain town.
Having arrived late, they room in an inn.\nThe next day...
I haven't seen her since last night.
That's strangeâ€”especially since we're\nsupposed to visit the local weapon shop\nthis morning.
Ramona strikes me as a dependable\nindividual. If she is not here on time,\nsomething unusual must have occurred.
We should check her room at once.
Sorry! Sorry! I know I'm crazy late!
It's good to see youâ€”we were all worried\nsomething terrible had happened.
So then, why were you not on time?
I would not have thought you the type.
I can scarce believe it myself.\nDid something happen last night\nthat made you overly tired?
Are you worried about something, maybe?
What, me? Nah. I slept like a fat baby\nafter a trip to a meat buffet.
Actually, I sorta...do that all the time.
It seems everyone holds a surprise or two.
Seeing how hard you work in the smithy,\nI never would have guessed.
But I'm super lazy whenever I'm not\non the jobâ€”probably to make up for it.
My sisters always have to wake me up.\nEr, and do a ton of other stuff for me.
Yeah, well, can we maybe stop talking\nabout it now? It's pretty embarrassing.
Let's go check out that weapon shop!\nChange of subject, la la laaaaa!
Sure thing. I think you'll enjoy itâ€”I was\nstunned by the quality of their lineup\nlast time I was there.
I can't wai... Huh? Oh man,\nlook at that clothing store!
She charged off toward that clothing store\nat maximum speed...
Let's go see what caught her eye.
Yeah, sorry for runnin' off like that.\nI just wanted to see these duds up close.
I don't think I've EVER been\nthis excited by clothing.
It's cuteâ€”which is another unexpected\nthing I have learned about you this day.
Likewise. I wouldn't have imagined you\nto be the fashion-oriented type.
Oh, this ain't for me to wearâ€”\nit's inspiration for my smithing!
Just look at that elegant stitchingâ€”\nand the delicate detail on the buttons!
It's clear that an exceptionally skilled\ntailor made thisâ€”which means it'll be\na great reference for my work!
It's always nice to meet those who\ncan appreciate true quality.
Do make certain to examine\nthe inner lining as well.
Our policy is to handle every part of our\nproducts with the same level of careâ€”\neven those you don't ordinarily see.
Thanks for lettin' me poke around.\nIt was really informative.
Oh, and I'll take every one'a these\nyou have in stock. Thanks!
Well, MY day just got made.
I'm glad you were able to find\nsomething that inspires you.
It ain't often you find somethin' with that\nlevel of craftsmanship AND design.
Yeah. To put it simply...it's super cute!
But did you not just say that your interest\ncame from using them as reference points\nfor your work, not for wearing them?
That's right. So I can make weapons that\nare cute instead of boorish.
Then this IS about fashion? Er, or not?\nI am very confused.
The more I learn about you, Ramona,\nthe less I understand you.
Eh, I ain't as tough to figure out\nas all that.
I just appreciate both good work\nAND cuteness when I see it!
